comments.text:
All this talk(or rather, outrage) about Knuckles voice being atered is simply uncalled for. First off, I want people to understand that I make videos for fun, it's an escape for me and the lifestyle that I live, and not every new voice in this video were going to be set in stone forever. I like to try new things all the time and sometimes they can be hit or miss. But that's what happens when people are afraid of change. Unlike you, I'm not. Because I know change happened. The voices I chose long ago for the cast weren't meant to be the voices until the end of time. They just happened to end up the way they did because it's just that. Something that happened. For example, if I could get Phil Hayes to voice Bartleby in my videos instead, I would do that in a heart beat. But such things are not possible, so I make do with what I have. 
The voice I chose for Knuckles this movie is closer to the voice of Knuckes the Echidna in the actual show of Sonic Underground, so that's why I did what I did. But then I remembered that I'm like the only person on earth who actually watched Sonic Underground, so I guess I should have expected something like this to happen. Now whether Knuckles voice changes back to the old one, I'm not sure yet because that's going to be something I decide on when I get to that point. But with that all that being said, those of you who were kind and announced your critisicm about the change respectfully, I want you all to know that I do hear you and of course I will always strive to make Sonic Underground something that everyone can enjoy. As for those petty babys that poop themselves who came and attacked me for the choices I made, you can suck my balls.

-Tamers1235
